Is there anyway to delete several objects without using much space?

What do I mean by this?

Is there anyway of deleting objects inbetween:
X: 2164 - 2138
Y: 5091 - 5106
Without having to every single one with this?
c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, 2164, 3138, 1, 10);

I’m trying to save space and would rather just have this entire area, empty.

I’m not the best coder, I’m still learning. But I tried making something like this.

if (absX >= x && absX <= x1 && absY >= y && absY <= y1) { int x = 2164; int x1 = 2138; int y = 5091; int y1 = 5106; c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, x, y, 1, 10); c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, x1, y1, 1, 10); }

This code probably is the worst way to do it, if it even works.
